d-upon-muttafaqun-alayhi","tag-family-ties-silat-rahim","tag-fear-al-khawf","tag-gentleness-al-rifq","tag-manners-adab","tag-night-al-layl","tag-travel-al-safr"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-420","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":15496,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/29\/travel-quickly-return-family\/","url_meta":{"origin":15500,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Return to family as fast as you can","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 29, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cTravel is a piece of torment. It prevents one of you from eating, drinking, and sleeping. When he has finished his purpose, let him quickly return to his family.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1804, Sahih Muslim 1927 Grade: Muttafaqun\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4362,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/07\/worship-jihad-ten-nights-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":15500,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: The Prophet strives in last ten nights","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 7, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: When the last ten nights of Ramadan arrived, the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would tighten his belt, spend the night in worship, and awaken his family. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 2024, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1174 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":943,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/07\/23\/spending-on-your-family-sadaqah\/","url_meta":{"origin":15500,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Sadaqah: Spending on your family is an act of charity","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Mas'ud reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"If a Muslim spends on his family seeking reward from Allah, it is charity for him.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5351, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1002 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2935,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/18\/death-only-his-deeds-remain\/","url_meta":{"origin":15500,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Death: After death, only his deeds remain","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThree things follow a deceased person. Two of them return and one remains. His family, his wealth, and his deeds follow him. His family and wealth return, but his deeds remain.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6149,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15377,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/24\/prophet-chooses-milk-not-wine\/","url_meta":{"origin":15500,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Fitrah: The Prophet chooses natural milk, not wine","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 24, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: On the night of the Ascension, the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was presented with two vessels, one full of wine and the other full of milk. The Prophet looked at them both, and he chose the vessel full of milk. The Angel\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":41207,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/09\/20\/missing-salat-al-asr\/","url_meta":{"origin":15500,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Salah: Warning against missing congregational \u2018Asr prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 20, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever misses the afternoon prayer, it is as if he had lost his family and his property.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 552, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u032